World / state x_t,Represent a system as a state evolving over time.,State-space modelling; control systems; POMDP framing,Institutional state; administrative record status; affected-person status,"Agent state, environment state, model activations/latent state","Provides a common object for harm, memory, correction, and future-space to act on.",known,Inherited formal vocabulary,,,,,,Memory persists across loops while the external day resets; learning survives repetition.,Memory as carrier of accountable iteration.,"The Creature has stakes, memory, language, pain, relation-need, and agency but is denied recognition.",Origin and appearance cannot erase a subject-claim.
Observation o_t,A local slice of reality available to an actor or system.,Signal detection; partial observability; Bayesian update,"Notice, complaint, inspection, whistleblowing, ombudsman signal","Telemetry, logs, eval traces, activation observations",Ties ethical failure to what the system can or cannot see in time.,known,Maps directly to witness/detection,"Telemetry, crew report, and anomaly signals become the first live view of the damaged system.","Foam strike was visible in launch imagery and identified on Flight Day 2, but the signal did not become a binding safety-of-flight problem.",Apollo: anomaly signal becomes a live command problem. Columbia: anomaly signal is seen but not made binding.,,,"Each loop creates local correction windows; some harms can be prevented, some limits remain.",Correction under repeated temporal reset.,"Victor hides the causal record, preventing contestable correction.","No record, no binding correction."
Memory / trusted record T(M),Continuity depends on records whose reliability can be challenged.,State estimation; feedback memory; data integrity,"Administrative records, evidence files, audit logs, appeal bundles","Training data, logs, chain-of-thought substitutes, provenance, trace capture","Makes record integrity part of identity/correction, not paperwork after the fact.",patterned,Memento anchor; not film-validated,"Mission logs, procedures, component histories, and telemetry preserve enough state to reason from.","Prior foam-shedding history and STS-107 debris analysis existed, but the record reinforced normalisation rather than forcing permission change.",Apollo: records/procedures support repair. Columbia: records/history support normalisation until post-accident inquiry.,,,Memory persists across loops while the external day resets; learning survives repetition.,Memory as carrier of accountable iteration.,"Victor hides the causal record, preventing contestable correction.","No record, no binding correction."
Constraint C,"A boundary on admissible states, actions, transitions, or methods.",Control constraints; safe set; viable region,"Rule of law, rights limits, proportionality, due process constraints","Policy constraints, refusal rules, deployment gates",ME emphasises constraints that survive pressure rather than preferences that optimise away.,known,Central ME operator,,,,,,Manipulative methods produce apparent success but not genuine relation or release.,Outcome appearance does not cleanse method.,"Capability launched without stewardship, correction, or decommissioning ethics risks destructive drift.",AI alignment bridge: creator convenience is not a duty map.
Action u_t / policy π,An actor selects an intervention from available options.,Control input; policy in decision theory/RL,Administrative discretion; delegated authority; institutional decision path,"Agent policy, tool-use policy, deployment action",Links ethical responsibility to selected state-change rather than stated intention.,known,"Standard notation, ME use is contextual",,,,,,Same conditions plus retained memory allow different branch-selection and self-update.,Operational free will under constraint.,Victor creates consequential life/power and refuses answerability.,Creation creates duties beyond technical success.
Method m_t,How an action is performed changes the resulting world state.,Process path-dependence; intervention channel,Procedural fairness; inadmissible methods; evidentiary contamination,"Tool choice, scaffolding, prompt/deployment method, data collection method",Distinctive emphasis: method is not neutral plumbing; it can be part of harm.,patterned,Strong ME/TRACE contribution candidate,"Survival depends on repair method: usable instructions, onboard materials, and no blame-before-repair closure.",Analysis method converted uncertainty into reassurance; requests for imagery and deeper analysis were channel-fragile rather than mission-binding.,Apollo: method expands option-space under constraint. Columbia: method narrows uncertainty into reassurance.,,,Manipulative methods produce apparent success but not genuine relation or release.,Outcome appearance does not cleanse method.,Creation without care and repair becomes abandonment as harm.,"Care is part of responsible activation, not optional sentiment."
Affected-subject modelling,"The system must model the state of those acted upon, not only operator goals.",Human-in-the-loop as observed state; stakeholder state variables,"Standing, burden, access, affected-person rights","Human feedback, user impact assessment, externalised harm telemetry","Routes the model toward the subject’s correction capacity, not just system performance.",patterned,Important bridge to administrative justice,"Crew state, life-support needs, available materials, and execution limits remain central to the model.","Crew survival state depended on wing integrity, but management framing treated the debris strike as an analysis/schedule issue more than a subject-side emergency.",Apollo keeps crew-state central. Columbia lets organisational framing dominate subject-state urgency.,,,"Each loop creates local correction windows; some harms can be prevented, some limits remain.",Correction under repeated temporal reset.,"The Creature has stakes, memory, language, pain, relation-need, and agency but is denied recognition.",Origin and appearance cannot erase a subject-claim.
K correction gate,"Correction exists only if witness, record, authority, time, enforcement, and repair are all live.",Feedback control; negative feedback; requisite response capacity,"Appeal, review, jurisdiction, enforceability, remedy","Incident response, rollback, eval-to-deploy feedback, safety case response paths",The AND-gate form is a compact ME remainder: any missing factor collapses effective correction.,candidate distinctive,K = W·R·A·Tm·E·Rp,"Witness, record, authority, time, enforcement, and repair stay connected through crew, Mission Control, and engineers.","Detection and partial record existed, but authority, time-use, enforcement, and repair did not stay conjunctively linked; the gate broke despite process.",Apollo keeps K factors linked. Columbia shows K can fail even when several factors are nominally present.,,,Memory persists across loops while the external day resets; learning survives repetition.,Memory as carrier of accountable iteration.,Victor creates consequential life/power and refuses answerability.,Creation creates duties beyond technical success.
Witness / detection W,Harm must be noticed by someone or something with enough signal access.,Sensor coverage; observability; detection latency,"Complaint route, inspection, whistleblower, public record","Monitoring, anomaly detection, red-team reports","Centres detection as an ethical precondition, not merely operational hygiene.",known,Part of K gate,The anomaly is detected through system signal and crew report rather than suppressed or narratively closed.,Witness existed: the Intercenter Photo Working Group saw an unusually large strike and concern existed inside engineering channels.,Both cases have signal. Discrimination depends on whether signal routes into authority and action.,,,Memory persists across loops while the external day resets; learning survives repetition.,Memory as carrier of accountable iteration.,Victor creates consequential life/power and refuses answerability.,Creation creates duties beyond technical success.
Record survival R,Evidence of what happened must survive long enough to support correction.,"Logging, traceability, system memory","Audit trail, case file, disclosure, evidentiary preservation","Logs, provenance, model snapshots, incident ledger","Makes lost records a correction failure, not an administrative inconvenience.",known,Part of K gate,"Telemetry, checklists, and engineering knowledge survive long enough to support correction.","Records survived after the fact, but during the mission the live record did not force the decision state to remain open.",Apollo: live record enables action. Columbia: record becomes more powerful after harm hardens.,,,Memory persists across loops while the external day resets; learning survives repetition.,Memory as carrier of accountable iteration.,"Victor hides the causal record, preventing contestable correction.","No record, no binding correction."
Authority / access A,Someone must have real power and standing to alter the path.,Actuator access; control authority,"Jurisdiction, standing, appeal right, delegated power","Rollback authority, deployment control, governance escalation",Separates seeing harm from being able to interrupt it.,known,Part of K gate,"Crew and Mission Control retain practical authority to change procedure, trajectory, power use, and life-support configuration.",Engineers and photo-analysis actors did not have sufficient authority/access to make imagery or safety reassessment bite before re-entry.,Apollo distributes authority to problem-solvers. Columbia leaves crucial actors without enough interrupt capacity.,,,,,Victor creates consequential life/power and refuses answerability.,Creation creates duties beyond technical success.
Time before hardening Tm,Correction must arrive before the relevant consequence becomes practically irreversible.,Control latency; real-time systems; deadline constraints,"Interim relief, injunction, limitation periods, urgency procedures","Fast rollback, kill switch, staged release, reversible deployment",ME’s clearest remainder: ethics is clocked; late review is often theatre.,candidate distinctive,Core correction-window idea,"Life-support, CO2, power, water, trajectory, and re-entry windows create hard correction deadlines.","Time existed during orbit, but it was not converted into executable correction before re-entry hardened the loss.",Apollo uses remaining time as repair-space. Columbia consumes remaining time as analysis/closure-space.,,,"Each loop creates local correction windows; some harms can be prevented, some limits remain.",Correction under repeated temporal reset.,Creation without care and repair becomes abandonment as harm.,"Care is part of responsible activation, not optional sentiment."
Enforcement / consequence carrier E,A correction rule must have a carrier that can bite against the actor with leverage.,Actuator effectiveness; control channel authority,"Sanctions, court orders, regulatory powers, contractual penalties","Deployment blocks, access revocation, audit consequences",Names the difference between nominal safeguards and real teeth.,patterned,Kindness/trust with teeth,"Operational command and mission procedure can make the chosen correction bite as executable action, not advice.","No correction carrier forced management to obtain imagery, reopen assumptions, or prove safety before proceeding to re-entry.",Apollo procedures make correction executable. Columbia lacks a carrier that makes uncertainty bite.,,,"Each loop creates local correction windows; some harms can be prevented, some limits remain.",Correction under repeated temporal reset.,Victor creates consequential life/power and refuses answerability.,Creation creates duties beyond technical success.
Repair capacity Rp,"Correction must be able to restore, compensate, or materially alter the harmed path.",Recovery dynamics; restoration; resilience,"Remedy, compensation, rectification, reinstatement","Rollback, redress, retraining, remediation workflow",Refuses symbolic review when the affected state remains damaged.,known,Part of K gate,"LiOH adapter, power-down procedures, trajectory correction, and re-entry preparation materially alter the path.","Possible response paths were uncertain and limited, but the practical failure begins earlier: the system did not preserve enough information/authority to know whether repair was needed.",Apollo repair reaches the subject. Columbia cannot reach repair because witness/authority/knowledge fail first.,,,"Each loop creates local correction windows; some harms can be prevented, some limits remain.",Correction under repeated temporal reset.,Victor creates consequential life/power and refuses answerability.,Creation creates duties beyond technical success.
τ_intervene < τ_harden,A safeguard is live only if it can change the path before hardening.,Latency bound; control before threshold crossing,Urgent relief before deprivation; meaningful hearing before irreversible loss,Safety intervention before deployment or autonomous cascade,Most portable ME formula: correction-before-hardening as a timing condition.,candidate distinctive,Diagnostic Kernel candidate,The core Apollo expression: working solutions must reach the crew before life-support or trajectory failure hardens.,Intervention did not beat hardening: uncertainty management continued while the re-entry deadline approached.,The pair is the kernel contrast: correction wins in Apollo; hardening wins in Columbia.,,,"Each loop creates local correction windows; some harms can be prevented, some limits remain.",Correction under repeated temporal reset.,Creation without care and repair becomes abandonment as harm.,"Care is part of responsible activation, not optional sentiment."
